SECTION 8 — HASH CHAIN & CRYPTOGRAPHIC INTEGRITY
Every event in the system is cryptographically hashed and linked to the previous event in the session, forming a tamper-evident chain identical in principle to a blockchain’s Merkle chain.
8.1 — Hash Computation Algorithm
function computeEventHash(event) {
  const payload = JSON.stringify({
    event_code: event.event_code,
    event_type: event.event_type,
    session_id: event.session_id,
    declared_by: event.declared_by,
    timestamp_utc: event.timestamp_utc,
    location_label: event.location_label,
    annotation_text: event.annotation_text || null,
    prev_event_hash: event.prev_event_hash || null,
  }, Object.keys(event).sort());  // deterministic key ordering

  return sha256(payload);  // Use Web Crypto API in Edge Functions
}

// Session hash = SHA-256 of concatenated event hashes in order
function computeSessionHash(eventHashes) {
  return sha256(eventHashes.join(':'));
}
