SECTION 11 — SECURITY REQUIREMENTS
•	All transport is HTTPS/TLS — no exceptions, including QR endpoints and anonymous access.
•	Edge Functions must validate all inputs (QR payloads, tokens, annotation text). Use Zod or equivalent.
•	Driver tokens: opaque UUIDs, 24-hour TTL, stored in a server-side token table with expiry column, validated on every request.
•	QR signatures: ECDSA P-256. Private key stored in Supabase secrets/vault. Public key embedded in verification logic.
•	Rate limiting: QR scan endpoint limited to 10 requests/minute per IP. Annotation endpoint limited to 5 requests/minute per token.
•	Input sanitization: all text fields (annotations, labels) are sanitized against XSS and SQL injection before storage.
•	RLS policies: facility users can only see their own facility’s data. Drivers can only access their own session via token. External verifiers can only access evidence_packets via hash.
•	No PII is stored for drivers. The driver_token is the ONLY identifier, and it is opaque.

